series exemplifies, occurs in the context of a wider shift in the nature and
concerns of the discipline. This paper begins with a short review of this
context and significant trends in the field. The review motivates and leads to
a set of requirements for support software of general utility for NLP research
and development workers. A freely-available system designed to meet these
requirements is described (called GATE - a General Architecture for Text
Engineering). Information Extraction (IE), in the sense defined by the Message
Understanding Conferences (ARPA \cite{Arp95}), is an NLP application in which
many of the new methods have found a home (Hobbs \cite{Hob93}; Jacobs ed.
\cite{Jac92}). An IE system based on GATE is also available for research
purposes, and this is described. Lastly we review related work.</api:text></api:field><api:field name="authors" type="person-list" display-name="Authors"><api:people><api:person><api:links><api:link type="elements/user" id="1851" href="https://mypublications.shef.ac.uk:8091/secure-api/v6.13/users/1851"/></api:links><api:last-name>Cunningham</api:last-name><api:initials>H</api:initials><api:first-names>Hamish</api:first-names><api:separate-first-names><api:first-name>Hamish</api:first-name></api:separate-first-names></api:person><api:person><api:last-name>Wilks</api:last-name><api:initials>Y</api:initials><api:first-names>Yorick</api:first-names><api:separate-first-names><api:first-name>Yorick</api:first-name></api:separate-first-names></api:person><api:person><api:links><api:link type="elements/user" id="2026" href="https://mypublications.shef.ac.uk:8091/secure-api/v6.13/users/2026"/></api:links><api:last-name>Gaizauskas</api:last-name><api:initials>RJ</api:initials><api:first-names>Robert J</api:first-names><api:separate-first-names><api:first-name>Robert</api:first-name><api:first-name>J</api:first-name></api:separate-first-names></api:person></api:people></api:field><api:field name="author-url" type="text" display-name="Link 1"><api:text>http://arxiv.org/abs/cmp-lg/9607025v1</api:text></api:field><api:field name="journal" type="text" display-name="Journal"><api:text>Proceedings of NEMLAP-2</api:text></api:field><api:field name="keywords" type="keyword-list" display-name="Keywords"><api:keywords><api:keyword>cmp-lg</api:keyword><api:keyword>cmp-lg</api:keyword><api:keyword>cs.CL</api:keyword></api:keywords></api:field><api:field name="notes" type="text" display-name="Other information"><api:text>12 pages, LaTeX, uses nemlap.sty (included)</api:text></api:field><api:field name="publication-date" type="date" display-name="Publication date"><api:date><api:day>23</api:day><api:month>7</api:month><api:year>1996</api:year></api:date></api:field><api:field name="record-c